GOSC 2012 Philip Herron - Cython
--------------------------------

Pxd generation via the gcc-python-plugin. This tool now requires users to use
GCC 4.7 or greater.

GCC installation - instructions:
Download GCC

untar
$ mkdir build
$ cd build
$ ../gcc/configure --enable-languages=c,. --enable-plugin <--disable-bootstrap/--enable-gold>
$ make
$ make install

GCC-python-plugin
$ export $(CC)="gcc" # make sure its your new GCC
$ make

Pxd-generation-tool
$ cp {gpxd.py, pycpp.py, pxdconfig.py} ~/gcc-python-plugin

# create a dummy C file:
<include all the headers you want to generate pxd for>

int main (int argc, char **argv)
{
  return 0
}

# edit pxdconfig.h:
output = "" # name of pxd file output
headers = [ ] # list of strings of headers you want to generate pxd for

$ gcc -fplugin=./python.so -fplugin-arg-python-script="gpxd.py" -O0 -c t.c

NOTE:

To generate code for system installed librarys, as in headers outside of your current
working directory. You must give full path names for example:

#include "/usr/include/gmp-i386.h"
...

And:

headers = [ '/usr/include/gmp-i386.h',
	    .... ]

This is because for macro parsing the macro parser requires a proper path to the header
it doesnt understand system path searching.

There is no working BLACKLIST yet, not quite sure how i want it to work.

